<section class="task-13 container">
  <h1 class="heading-orange" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
    Fake News<br />
    Detectors:<br />
    Benefits and<br />
    Limitations
  </h1>

  <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
    In this badge, you have learned about the problems and 
    dangers of fake news and how these are worsened by the 
    explosion of the internet and social media. The ability 
    for anyone to be able to publish news on the internet and 
    on social media platforms is enabling fake news to be spread 
    at an unprecedented rate and is also making it harder for 
    readers to spot the difference between what is real and what 
    is fabricated.
  </p>

  <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
    Fake news detectors utilise AI technology to detect fake 
    news on our behalf and have the potential to scan and sort 
    through large amounts of news articles in a much shorter 
    time than humans can, with a high level of accuracy. 
    AI-powered fake news detectors can be extremely useful 
    but there are also weaknesses to be mindful of, whether 
    you are designing your own fake news detector or using one. 
  </p>

  <div class="activity-box pad-widow" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">

    <h2 class="inherit" style="font-weight: bold" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
      Can you identify which of the following statements are benefits or limitations of fake news detectors?
    </h2>

    <p class="example" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
      You will start this game with three lives. If you run out 
      of lives before you finish the game, you will have to 
      start over.
    </p>

    <div class="reflection" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-delay="150">
      <div class="reflection__progress">
        <p class="reflection__counter">1/9</p>
        <p class="reflection__lives">
          <strong>
            Lives Remaining: <span class="jsLives"></span>
          </strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reflection__statements__container">
        <button class="reflection__control reflection__control--previous hide">
          <img src="/badge-assets/fake-news/svg/previous.svg" width="25" height="25" alt="Previous slide" />
        </button>

        <button class="reflection__control reflection__control--next hide">
          <img src="/badge-assets/fake-news/svg/next.svg" width="25" height="25" alt="Next slide" />
        </button>

        <div class="reflection__statements">
          <p>Look at other models to see if you can improve on the 98% accuracy rating</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="reflection__options">
        <li class="reflection__options__option">
          <input id="limitation" name="choice-1" type="radio" value="Limitation" />
          <label for="limitation" class="reflection__options__choice"> Limitation </label>
        </li>

        <li class="reflection__options__option">
          <input id="benefit" name="choice-1" type="radio" value="Benefit" />
          <label for="benefit" class="reflection__options__choice"> Benefit </label>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="success-box hide" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
      Nicely done! You have successfully identified the benefits and limitations of fake news detectors.
    </p>

    <p class="fail-box hide">Oops... You have no lives remaining. You will have to start from the begining.</p>
  </div>
</section>
